"Come with Me" is a song recorded by Puerto Rican singer-songwriter Ricky Martin for his upcoming studio album. It was produced by the Australian duo DNA Songs (Anthony Egizii and David Musumeci) and IIan Kidron from The Potbelleez. "Come with Me" premiered on June 13, 2013, during the The Kyle and Jackie O Show in Australia and was digitally released worldwide on June 14, 2013. Martin performed the song on the grand finale of The Voice in Australia on June 17, 2013 where he was one of the coaches.On July 18, 2013, Martin performed a Spanglish version of the song at the 2013 Premios Juventud and released it digitally after the ceremony.On July 28, 2013, he also sang it on the finale of the La Voz Kids.Martin filmed two music videos for "Come with Me" on July 19, 2013. The video for the Spanglish Version premiered on August 14, 2013 on Univision.One week later, on August 21, 2013, both videos for the English and Spanglish Version were published on Vevo.
